The Imo State Governor Rochas Okorocha has sacked 13 political office holders in the state, including the Secretary to the State Government, George Eche, and Chief of Staff to the governor, Uche Nwosu, who is also his son-in-law. A statement issued in Owerri by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Sam Onwuemeodo, disclosed that the affected appointees are seeking elective positions on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC). ”The dismissed appointees are the ones who are seeking to contest in the coming 2019 elections,” Mr Onwuemeodo further said. Those affected appointees are: George Eche, Secretary to the Government of Imo State; Chief Uche Nwosu, Chief of Staff, Government House; Dr. Paschal Chigozie Obi, Principal Secretary to the Governor; Kingsley Uju, Deputy Chief of Staff (Operations); Chief Emma Ojinero, Commissioner for Trade & Investment/Commerce and Prof. Nnamdi Obiareri, Commissioner for Information. Also affected are: Mrs Ngozi Njoku, Commissioner for Gender/Social Development; Lady Joy Mbawuike, Commissioner for Market Development; Obinna Mbata, Commissioner for Finance; Dr. Dan Nworie, Commissioner for Tertiary Education; Simeon Iwunze, Special Adviser on Urban Renewal; Obinna Amagwula, Special Assistant General Duties as well as Mrs Betty Uzoma, Special Assistant Finance. Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 